Liberty Global Considers Buying Dutch Cable TV Operator Ziggo, FT Reports

-- B y   B l a n c h e   G a t t
-- 
2011-04-11T02:10:02Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-11/liberty-global-considers-dutch-cable-company-ziggo-ft-reports.html
Liberty Global Inc. (LBTYA) ’s Chief
Strategy Officer Shane O’Neill is working out whether the
company can afford to acquire Ziggo BV, the Dutch cable operator
owned by private-equity companies Cinven Ltd. and Warburg Pincus
LLC, the Financial Times reported, citing O’Neill’s remarks
following the agreement to buy Kabel Baden-Wurttemberg GmbH &
Co. from EQT.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Blanche Gatt in London at 
 bgatt@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Colin Keatinge at 
 ckeatinge@bloomberg.net . 